@node Shareware "Phonemaster is shareware, please respect it."

	@{u}Yup!	Phonemaster is Shareware...@{uu}
	
	I have spent 'Tons' of time creating this Application, 
	trying to make as user-friendly and yet use/powerfull, 
	is not always the easiest thing to do... 

	So if you use Phonemaster at a regulary basis, 
	you should register as a user, and support my hard work...
	Thereby securing future versions of your favorite address manager! ;·)

	Since I know Shareware fee's never get paid, by so many people. (HINT!)
	I have set it as low as: 6.0 US$. Or 30 Danish crowns. ;·)
		- Of'coz you put enough stamps on the envelope, eh?


             NOTE! - This piece of software ain't crippled!!!



	@{u}Message to people who don't register:@{uu}
	·Just don't get surprised if you don't see any major improvements!!!

	If you don't want to pay the shareware fee, then don't pay! 
	But please register as a user anyway, so I know you are out there...
	As I have spent almost a year, on finetuning Phonemaster,
	I sure think 6$, is very cheap, considering the worth, 
	of a little flexible address manager, like phonemaster... 
	Almost every code-line has been rewritten many times, to make phonemaster 
	as reliable, and trustworthy, and most of all: as @{u}User-friendly!!!@{uu}
	As it has become today...

	@{u}Write to me for Registration, Bug reporting or Contacting...@{uu} 
	
	@{" Jump to Fini 'Warp' Alring's Info-page... " link Warp}		

@endnode

@node Introduction "What is Phonemaster anyway?"

	Phonemaster is a GUI controlled database, 
	designed for handling information about persons and companies...
	
	
	Why Phonemaster v5.xx? Why have I never heard of it?

	Since I got my Amiga (1991), I have always wanted to maintain my
	friends phonenumber's and address's, on my amiga...
	
	So I developed my own program, for the purpose...

		And thus Phonemaster was born!!!

	The older versions (v1.xx - v4.xx) were only used by myself, and members of GiGA Prod. 
	Because of it's strange source,format,structure... :-)
	
 	And now I finally released a public version, for you to use... (v5.54)
 	
 	Hence the name Phonemaster v5.xx! Also called PM5 or Phonemaster 5000!
	
@endnode


@node Required "Do I have everything I need?"

	
	@{u} Required Operating System: @{uu} 
		AmigaOS v2.04+. (I haven't tested it on v2.04, but I think it works!)
	
	@{u} Required files: @{uu}

	C:
		PM5 - This is a script that starts up Phonemaster.
		
	PM5:
		Main.pm5	 - The program itself.
		PM5.guide	 - This guide!
		PM5.Prefs  - The config file.
		Prefs.pm5  - The prefs ext. Module. (Used by Main.pm5)  
		Data (Dir) - The drawer in which all the Phone-files lie.
		
	
	System programs:
	 	Rexxmast - The Arexx interpretor MUST be running. 
		Multiview - To view the phonelist and read the guide, and view the phonelist. 
		(Amigaguide - can be used instead of Multiview, if you have AmigaOS 2.xx). 
		@{I}(Multiview and Amigaguide can be Either in 'Sys:Utilities/', 'Sys:Utils/', or 'C:'). @{UI}
		
	Libs:
		Reqtools.library - Needed to render the GUI. 
		RexxReqtools.library - Needed to contact Reqtools via Arexx.
		
	Font:
		I suggest Xhelvetica.font/11, as this font was used, when creating PM5.
		And I have trouble making TAB spaces, with reqtools!?...Can ye help?
		But feel free, to use another font...
		(The Xhelvetica.font is part of the MagicWB compilation).
		BTW - This guide tries to use Xhelvetica.font/11 too. 


	Everything should be available on AmiNet, and several other places...
	
@endnode



@node Features "Features.  (No special order!)"

		·Phonemaster features a complete multitasking/threading 
		 requester driven GUI-system, using Arexx and Rexx/Reqtools.library

		The current @{" Phone-file format " link "Phoneformat"} supports:

		·Names. 
		·Address string.
		·Home and Mobile phonenumbers.
		·E-mail Address.
		·CPR-number (Format: DDMMYY) 
		·Unlimited comments. (Ain't no novel gonna be written here!!! :·)  
		·Encrypted comments. (Use PGP for Top secret material!)
 
		·Each Entry is stored in it's own phone-file (ASCII), 
		 this makes it easy to copy a set of phone-files from a friend, 
		 to one's own AMIGA.

		·Phonemaster uses an open ASCII-file-format, 
		 which is very easy to learn, and use in other programs, 
		 such as your own, or arexx-script's for other programs.

		·Can Create, Edit and Kill (Delete) Phone-files... 

		·Can be set to use any bitmap AMIGA-OS font.

		·Can generate a Phonelist for Printing, Saving or just Viewing.  

		·Features An On-line help-service at any time!
		
		·Comes with Dopus v5.xx Filetype.

		·Can be used entirely by keyboard shortcuts!

		·Interpretes CPR-numbers such as 231277 to:	'23 December 1977    (Age: XX)'

		·Birthday alert, tells you up to 30 days before and after.
		
		·Uses internal multithreading for multiple windows/sessions etc.

		·Give's you info about the current date, week and time.


		·And much more...! :-) 

		- @{" Warp " link Warp} to @{" Main " link main}

@endnode


@node Usage "Where and how can I start PM5?"

Different ways to start phonemaster:

	C:PM5 {Enter}
 
	C:PM5 Filename {Enter}
	

To start phonemaster in Direct-call mode:

	C:PM5 * {Enter}

	This will start PM5 up, with a instant Call-requester, instead of starting up in the main menu.
	
	@{i}I use this function in conjuction with a hotkey (eg. Shift F9). @{ui} 

	From workbench you can also use the icons:
	
	Phonemaster! 	- Brings up the main menu. (C:PM5)
	
	Phonemaster!!! 	- Starts in direct-call mode. (C:PM5 *)


Make sure PM5: is assigned to your main Phonemaster drawer.
	eg. 'Assgin PM5: Sys:tools/Phonemaster/'

Also make sure you have all files required, the right places...
@endnode


@node Notes "Small notes, about phonemaster's system..."


@{u}Filenames:@{uu}
	The characters: ':' '/' '|' will automatically be replaced with ';' & '_'.
	But the original name will also be stored in the phone-file.
	This is because AmigaDOS uses these characters for other purposes. (eg. Df0:)  

	NOTE!: Do NOT use '()' in the filename either.


@{u}Phone-Files:@{uu}
	Files which has the Delete Protection-Bit set, cannot be Killed from PM5.
	Though you can still delete it from AmigaDOS, Dopus etc.
	If you choose to edit a protected file, you can choose if you still
	want it to be protected.


	The @{" Phone-file format " link "Phoneformat"} has intentionally been made 
	in a very simple Ascii format (HTML stylish?), which any programmer can learn. 
	Thereby he/she can use the data of the phone-files, for other purposes.
	Click above to learn about it. Best of all, try to mess around with it.


@{u}Fonts:@{uu}
	Phonemaster was designed to use Xhelvetica.font/11, but you can use whatever
	font you like, BUT beware! RexxReqtools doesn't seem to handle TAB-Spaces!
	So it might look very strange with other fonts. (I'll try to fix it).


@{U}Lingua?@{UU}
	If you want to make/get translations for PM5, then tell me, but it will only be
	done if I get requests for it, by enough people.
	Since it will take some manpower to code and translate it!

@endnode


@node History "History."

@{u} Phonemaster revision history: @{uu} 	

  To check how new your version is, please refer to Info, in the program.

  NOTE: Revision number is also updated, when I make private updates.

	SHORT = Short message about the release.
	FIXED = Fixed
	ADDED = New
	REMOV = Removed
	REWRI = Rewritten
	OVERW = Overworked
	IMPRO = Improved
	REPLA = Replaced

               ·············································

	v5.57 - FIXED   A bug when aborting a file-req.

		   REPLA   Fini.jpeg with Fini.png. - I hated the JPEG one! ;-D	

		   FIXED   PM5 no longer dead-locks if #E tag is missing, in a file.

		   ADDED   Encrypted messages. Only numeric password's (1000-888888888).
				 Do @{B}not@{UB} use this encryption, for @{B}TOP SECRET@{UB} material.
			      It is possible to write a decrypter, but it will be hard!
				 Please send one, if you find/make one! ;-D
		           Note: It is the first version of the Crypter, so be cautious!!!

	v5.56 - SHORT   Enhanced the Birthday Alert, Changed the Info part.

		   IMPRO   Can now look backwards, and see if someone just had birthday.  

		   ADDED   You can set the number of days to check back/forwards in time.

		   IMPRO   The info part has been changed, for better usage.

	v5.55 - ADDED   If Multiview wasn't found, PM5 will look for Amigaguide (OS 2.xx). 

	v5.54 - SHORT   1st AmiNET release. 02 Feb 1997

		   FIXED   Major bug, I made in v5.53, that's what happens,
		           when you code at demo parties... (Insomnia!;·) Sorry! TP96 rewled!

	v5.53 - SHORT   First public release. · The Party 1996 - 27-29 Dec!  

		   ADDED   Support for multi-select req's, open unl. wind's in a go! 
		           Due lack of sleep, I never tested this version any good.
			      It had a major bug, Sorry Death Row, I hope you didn't spread it. :-}

	@{B}All versions beneath this line was Beta versions, which was never released outside GiGA Prod.@{UB}

	v5.52ß - Now you can protect your files from being killed, with PM5.
	v5.51ß - Made a config file, and support module (Prefs.pm5), for PM5. 
			 You can only set fonts at the moment, but it will grow.
	v5.50ß - Wasted first multithread, and made the real PM5-Multithread. 
	v5.49ß - First prototype of PM5-Multithread was enabled.
	v5.48ß - C:PM5 Args now allow both 'C:PM5 Fini A. Alring' 
			and 'C:PM5 Dh0:Phonemaster/Data/Fini A. Alring' (A ':' must exist!)
			Prototype of PM5-Multithread has been made. (Not enabled yet!)
	v5.47ß - Simple Birthday Alert!, tells you up to one week before.
			Halt protection added.
	v5.46ß - Added Insert/Remove gadget in GetComments(),
			Improved Phone-file format, PMRead() and PMWrite().
	v5.45ß - Rewrote'n'Improved GetComments(), All-over bug fixes.
	v5.44ß - Rewrote the Kill function.
	v5.43ß - Won't go back to main menu, when Call/Kill is Aborted.
	v5.42ß - Fixed Prev-gadget in comment mode, Filename bug, C:PM5 2.0.
	v5.41ß - Bugfixed code, Redesigned PM5-argument-handler.
	v5.40ß - Impr. Source'n'Guide.  
	v5.39ß - Impr. Source, thus more speed, more reliable and better Quality!
	v5.38ß - More Info, AmigaGuide®-gadget added.
	v5.37ß - Added more info, about current day, in the Info gadget.
	v5.36ß - Double check-kill-func(), If filename='*' then pop filereq!. ('PM5 * {enter}')
	v5.35ß - bugfixes and improvements in the code.
	v5.34ß - Added E-mail support, and enhanced the On-line help.
	v5.33ß - Renamed Main 'Help' gadget to 'Info', with Date'n'Time info. 
	v5.32ß - Renamed Modify button to Edit... Thanx soURce!!!
	v5.31ß - Improved the On-line help, and much other text:·D + TAB-BUG! 

	All the past versions from v5.00ß-5.30ß were early ßeta-versions, 
	which died long before, the birth of this guide...
	



@{u} Phonemaster vX.xx development history: @{uu} 

	'90	At first, I used notebook, CygnusED and other ascii-editors.	
	
	'91	When I had learned something about AmigaDOS, I designed Phonemaster v1.0
			This was totally based, on AmigaDOS batch files.	
			
	'93	Phonemaster v2.0, featured an Auto-executer made in Arexx.	
	
	'94	Phonemaster v3.0 was a total recode, made in arexx. Still Cli-Based.	
	
	'94	Phonemaster v4.0 featured a GUI overlay (for v3.0), and many specials.
	&95	This was the last version which supported OLD Phone-files (All of them!).
	
	'96	Phonemaster v5.0 features New arexx code/design, Reqtools support, New Phone-files. 
		This program is very user-friendly and features On-line help + Guide! :·)
	
	The Party 1996 (27-29 Dec) - 
		After a year of development It's ready for a first release... 
	
	
		
	
		
	
	
	




			The text below is cut-out of old Phonemaster document:

					@{u}How it really started@{uu}


		Once in late 1991, I was sick for about one month and I thought;
		I'll try to create some sort of program. (W'96 - That's when I began to program ;·D )
		Well I came up with a disk based script program, using simple 
		AmigaDOS commands (Ed,Echo,Type,Execute). for some years I just
		polished the program, until I learned some Arexx (Late'93).
		I made a routine that would prevent me from having to type
		execute (X) infront of the phone-files, soon I was writing a
		whole Operating System for my dear PhoneMaster, Adv. Search functions,
		phone-file creator (Before I made'em all manually), comment-adder,
		Phone-file Handle Creator (PHC) - For the people with different
		nicknames etc...
		
      I'm glad that I made the old shit, coz I got better doing it!!!


	
				- @{"Warp" link Warp} to @{"Main" link Main}


@endnode



@node Future  "The future of Phonemaster."

	Remember:
		All future work depends on the response from you, The users!
		Support me with Blessings, cool ideas, bug-reports and money!
	
	Future plans/ideas for Phonemaster:

		More object oriented, file-format:
			- Unl. number's,Names,Addy's.
			- Custom numbers. eg. Work: 555-544-65, Bob's Mom: 555-544-54. 
			- Hidden comment's, which only decrypts with a unique password (Don't expect PGP here!).
			- Custom print. eg. Print Name+E-mail list, Print Name+Address+Phone etc.
			
		PGP support:
			Option to include peoples PGP key in the Phone-file,
			(You can do this now too, but you'll have to do it manually:·)
			I am also thinking about making EasyPGP?, with GUI and all!
			(But I just found a GUI for PGP on AmiNET called PGPgoesMUI! So I might hesitate).
			
		Speaker control:
			- Simulates the tones of your phone, so all you have to do,
			  is put you phone near the speakers, and it will dial for you...
			  @{I}This should not take long now, I just need the samples!@{UI}
			  
		Number reader:
			- This uses the narrator.device, and a homemade program,
			  to read the phonenumber's in english. eg. 'The number is...39...68...28...45'
 
 		Auto dialer:
			- Enable phonemaster to dial a number via, a modem.
			  (Since I don't have a modem, it might take a while ß·©. )
			  
		Birth constellation: (What is this called in english?)
			- Tells you if a person is a Capricorn, Virgin, Weight etc.
 
		Phonemaster V6.0:
			- New code made in C or Java?, 100% Multithreading,
			- Cool user-interface (GUI maybe MUI?), Arexx port!!!
			
@endnode


